1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,360
- Stay away from my sister!
- Samut!

2
00:02:56,040 --> 00:02:58,240
I love you more than any other man.

3
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,960
I have no right to you at all.

4
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:03,800
Do you even realize what you're saying?

5
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,040
I'm the one who brought Fahsai here.

6
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:08,640
I'll be the one taking her back.

7
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:10,840
You really don't understand
a damn thing, do you?

8
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,400
So what's the truth

9
00:03:18,080 --> 00:03:20,000
about Peeraka's body?

10
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,240
Samut.

11
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:37,960
I told you before.

12
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:41,760
I'm on your side,
if you're not ready to see anyone.

13
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:43,440
Thank you.

14
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,320
Right now, Mr. Mahasamut Pasukampanart

15
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,960
is campaigning inside the market.

16
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:53,280
But aside from his policies,
there's another issue

17
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:56,920
the public is paying
a lot of attention to.

18
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,760
Let's go ask him about it.

19
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,080
Hello, Mr. Mahasamut.

20
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:05,600
Is Ms. Fahsai not joining you today?

21
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:09,800
Well, Fahsai has been
working really hard lately,

22
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:11,000
so she's not feeling well.

23
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:13,320
I told her to take some time off.

24
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,680
Isn't it actually because the two of you

25
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,920
are in conflict
over her relationship with Mr. Dharn?

26
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,480
No, not at all.

27
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:25,000
Fahsai is an adult.

28
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,560
We each focus on our work for the party

29
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:29,560
and for the people.

30
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,360
- Alright.
- There's no issue between us.

31
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:32,440
It's not a big deal.

32
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:33,920
- Really?
- Yes.

33
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,280
- Excuse me.
- Oh, wait.

34
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:36,760
- Excuse us.
- This matter…

35
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:37,800
- Excuse us.
- The public is interested in this.

36
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:38,880
Excuse us.

37
00:04:40,040 --> 00:04:41,480
Hello, everyone.

38
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:44,000
Today we're keeping it light.

39
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:46,520
We've got a short film for you to enjoy.

40
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,280
- Can I take a photo?
- Of course.

41
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,120
I love you.

42
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,840
Thank you.

43
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,640
You're so handsome.

44
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,760
Thank you.

45
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:57,600
Wait, our <i>Mad Dog News</i>
is screening movies now?

46
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,720
Of course. It's just a short one.

47
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,240
Short is fine,

48
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,480
but is it good?

49
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,680
That's for our viewers to decide.

50
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:10,400
- Okay.
- Thank you so much.

51
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,160
- Thank you.
- So handsome.

52
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,560
- Thank you so much.
- Let me take one more photo.

53
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,240
Thank you.

54
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:31,760
What?

55
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:32,960
I'm taking a photo with him.

56
00:05:33,560 --> 00:05:35,440
Look.

57
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:37,400
Hey.

58
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,920
- Why is it like this?
- We shouldn't have supported him.

59
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,840
- Jon.
- I liked him.

60
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:41,760
- Yes, sir.
- Look.

61
00:05:41,840 --> 00:05:43,520
- What's going on?
- It's bad.

62
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,800
That's thug behavior right there.

63
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:55,160
What a disappointment.

64
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:58,360
And he dares to preach unity?

65
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,760
Mr. Mahasamut.

66
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:02,600
- Look.
- This way, please.

67
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,800
This way, please.

68
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,680
This way, sir.

69
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:07,720
Hey! What the hell
is that supposed to be?!

70
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:11,320
Are you a boxer or a politician?

71
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,920
Hey!

72
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,040
Who the hell leaked that clip?

73
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:27,400
Hey, you didn't know about this?

74
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,800
We were on set together all day yesterday.

75
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,560
Why are you even asking?

76
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:39,080
- Mr. Dharn is here.
- Here he is.

77
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:40,920
Mr. Dharn.

78
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:42,800
Can we get a statement?

79
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,560
- Can we have an interview?
- Yes.

80
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:47,760
Regarding the video
released by the Mad Dog Gang,

81
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:50,320
did you really get into a fight
with Mr. Mahasamut?

82
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,120
Let me clarify first.

83
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:57,960
The photos of me and Ms. Fahsai
outside the city,

84
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:00,800
it was purely coincidental.

85
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,520
Coincidence or fate?

86
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,720
Coincidence.

87
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,400
When I met her,

88
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:12,080
I invited her to dinner.

89
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:13,640
The rest is what you saw in the clip.

90
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:20,280
Then why did Mr. Mahasamut
punch you?

91
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:23,080
I'm not entirely sure.

92
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:26,440
I think he misunderstood something
about me and Ms. Fahsai.

93
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:28,320
<i>Why didn't you press charges?</i>

94
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:32,120
<i>It's out of consideration</i>
<i>for Ms. Fahsai and her family.</i>

95
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,800
<i>I'd prefer we talk things through</i>
<i>before turning it into a legal matter.</i>

96
00:07:37,480 --> 00:07:40,800
<i>Have you spoken yet?</i>

97
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:42,160
<i>Not yet.</i>

98
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:45,920
<i>I've been trying to contact Ms. Fahsai,</i>
<i>but I haven't been able to reach her.</i>

99
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:51,480
<i>If anyone can reach Ms. Fahsai,</i>

100
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:54,360
<i>please tell her to contact me.</i>

101
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,520
<i>I'm very worried about her.</i>

102
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:02,440
<i>And you're not holding a grudge</i>
<i>about Mr. Mahasamut hurting you?</i>

103
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:05,120
<i>Violence is never right.</i>

104
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,240
<i>I don't support it.</i>

105
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:11,640
<i>And if Mr. Mahasamut is watching</i>

106
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:14,920
<i>and wants to take responsibility</i>
<i>by apologizing,</i>

107
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,960
<i>I'm open to talking.</i>

108
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:22,840
Damn it.

109
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,280
Normally,

110
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,840
Mr. Mahasamut is a very polite person.

111
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:44,320
He never lets his emotions
get the better of him.

112
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,640
No matter how hard he works,

113
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:48,800
he's never hot-tempered.

114
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:51,480
Then what about the clip

115
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,720
released by <i>Mad Dog News</i>?

116
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:54,680
Yes.

117
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:58,000
I feel very sorry for Mr. Dharn.

118
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:01,880
But I'd like everyone not to judge

119
00:09:01,960 --> 00:09:03,520
based on only one side of the story.

120
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:08,360
Can you tell us the reason behind it?

121
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:10,120
Can you?

122
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,560
Please tell us.

123
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:16,040
This should be clarified
by the party and Mr. Mahasamut himself.

124
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:16,960
MS. MAYSA

125
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:19,080
But I'm sure everyone remembers

126
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:22,200
how he helped that employee at the club

127
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:25,160
and all the charity work he's done.

128
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:28,920
He's sacrificed so much.

129
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:32,880
I believe every action
has a reason behind it.

130
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:36,480
So I just want to show my support.

131
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,600
We're here to support you

132
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:40,440
and Mr. Mahasamut.

133
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:42,720
Please tell him to stay strong.

134
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:45,080
And you too.

135
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,400
Thank you.

136
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,840
Thank you so much.

137
00:09:48,520 --> 00:09:49,880
That is so obviously staged.

138
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:50,880
Oh.

139
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,720
That's the country's top leading actress.

140
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,320
How can you say that?

141
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,000
Look at this.

142
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,680
There are only a few reporters here.

143
00:10:00,760 --> 00:10:03,240
They were clearly handpicked.
And listen to the questions.

144
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,800
No one asked whether he used force,

145
00:10:07,880 --> 00:10:10,160
punched someone, or resorted to violence.

146
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,560
The nerd's smarter than you now.

147
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,360
What about the fans?

148
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,440
When we love a celebrity,

149
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:22,160
we love whoever they love too.

150
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,320
When your side slips,

151
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:27,080
you have to build
a positive narrative for yourself.

152
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:29,280
Mahasamut knows that.

153
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:32,080
That's why he is dating an actress.

154
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,560
Being a minister's son has its perks.

155
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:37,640
Even when he acts completely unstable,
good one second, bad the next,

156
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,360
his girlfriend goes this far to help him.

157
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,240
Peeraka had been saying lately

158
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:48,280
that he was under a lot of stress.

159
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:51,680
Being an intern is hard,

160
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:55,680
and he also had
some problems with his sister.

161
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,080
I'll do it.

162
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,320
Alright.

163
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:17,800
You really are a saint.

164
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:21,160
Normally you complain
about Mr. Samut all the time.

165
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,160
Complaining is one thing.

166
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:28,480
But times like this
are exactly when he needs me.

167
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,000
For men,

168
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:32,640
when they're winning, they get arrogant
and stop seeing your value.

169
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:36,360
But when they fall,
and you're the one standing beside them,

170
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,080
that's when

171
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:40,960
they realize they can't do without you.

172
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:45,320
I thought I'd hear something
more romantic than that.

173
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:51,960
Turns out it's just a game.

174
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,440
Anything romantic

175
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,920
expires after the first three months.

176
00:11:57,880 --> 00:12:00,280
If a couple wants to survive,

177
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,400
it's all about balancing importance.

178
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:06,160
The moment he stops
seeing your value, it's over.

179
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:08,800
Right.

180
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:11,520
So right now, you're very important.

181
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:15,120
But hypothetically,

182
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,680
if the one who loses value
is Mr. Samut, then what?

183
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:21,880
If he loses his MP seat,

184
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:24,880
will your relationship survive?

185
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,080
Whether he's an MP or not

186
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,760
doesn't matter.

187
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,880
He already has everything.

188
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:40,160
And next time, don't bring up
pointless hypotheticals like that.

189
00:12:40,880 --> 00:12:43,280
Something this small won't take him down.

190
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,160
Thank you so much, Maysa,

191
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,000
for going on camera to support Samut.

192
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:06,360
We're family, Dad.

193
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,360
I'm happy to do this for the family.

194
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:14,160
- Thank you so much.
- Of course.

195
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:17,240
Mr. Mahasamut, stay strong.
We're rooting for you.

196
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:19,440
These are for you.

197
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:21,600
Oh.

198
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,320
Thank you.

199
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:26,560
You're even more handsome
in person than on TV.

200
00:13:27,760 --> 00:13:30,520
- Thank you.
- Could we take a photo with you?

201
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,160
Of course.

202
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,800
Excuse me.
Could you take the picture for us?

203
00:13:43,800 --> 00:13:44,960
Alright.

204
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,440
One, two.

205
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:01,600
Anyway, thank you very much for today.

206
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:06,440
I have work this afternoon,
so I won't be able to take you myself.

207
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,520
I'll have Jon drive you instead.

208
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:11,080
Okay.

209
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,640
Do you need something?

210
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,280
See you after work.

211
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:25,600
Okay.

212
00:14:35,920 --> 00:14:38,720
Have you arranged the car
to take Fahsai to the doctor yet?

213
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:41,080
Yes, sir. It's ready.

214
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,000
Don't forget.

215
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:46,240
You must keep this confidential.

216
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:48,280
Yes, sir.

217
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,800
I'm trying not to think about it,

218
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:02,000
but the image
just keeps replaying in my head.

219
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,040
And whenever I remember it…

220
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:06,480
I feel disgusted.

221
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:11,040
You feel very disturbed by what happened.

222
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,080
Yes.

223
00:15:15,240 --> 00:15:17,720
I keep trying to remember
the good things my brother did for me,

224
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,240
and then I wonder

225
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,360
if all the times he was kind to me

226
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:26,040
was because I was his sister, or…

227
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:30,600
Dad says it was…
It was all a misunderstanding.

228
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,640
But it makes me think of…

229
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:45,080
a woman I helped at the foundation.

230
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,920
She couldn't bring herself
to tell anyone that…

231
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:58,960
that…

232
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:04,600
her own brother had abused her…

233
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:10,560
until she got pregnant.

234
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:20,480
But now I understand
why she never told anyone.

235
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:23,960
Because no one wants to believe

236
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:26,200
something like that
could happen in their own family.

237
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,400
That's why there are parents
who refuse to believe it

238
00:16:29,480 --> 00:16:31,280
and refuse to accept that it happens.

239
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,560
I'd like you

240
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:39,680
to think back to when
you were helping that case.

241
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:42,200
How did you see the situation then?

242
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:46,360
I told her that…

243
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:56,200
the one who should be ashamed

244
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:59,960
is the person who did something like that.

245
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,760
Yes, I'll come to the meeting right away.

246
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,200
Make two photocopies of this for me.

247
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:17,520
Sure.

248
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,240
Thanks.

249
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,720
You must be tired from reading scripts.

250
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,760
And with all the news
about Mr. Mahasamut too.

251
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,360
Thank you.

252
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:00,840
Well, when you're dating a politician,

253
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:03,440
what choice do you have

254
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:05,640
other than being his support system?

255
00:18:07,840 --> 00:18:09,120
Don't run, Raka!

256
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:11,080
Raka, please don't run.

257
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,920
I'm begging you. Turn yourself in.

258
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,400
You called the police?

259
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:18,080
Why? I told you already, I didn't do it.

260
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,280
Whether you did or not,

261
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:20,880
turn yourself in and fight the case.

262
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:23,600
There's no way you can escape anyway.

263
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,520
These aren't people you can go up against.

264
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,440
That makes me want to become
a politician right away.

265
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:38,080
Then,

266
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:41,160
you'd probably become a young,
single politician

267
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:45,320
with fangirls all over the country.

268
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,360
Sorry about that.

269
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,560
- Excuse me for a moment.
- Sure.

270
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,120
Hello, Mr. Rakchart.

271
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,680
I've obtained the information
about Ms. Fahsai.

272
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:52,920
At first, the hospital
refused to release it,

273
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:54,480
but I managed to get it.

274
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:01,000
Have you arranged the car
to take Fahsai to the doctor?

275
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:03,360
Yes, sir. It's ready.

276
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:04,920
Don't forget.

277
00:20:05,960 --> 00:20:08,040
You must keep this confidential.

278
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,720
THE PATIENT
IS SUFFERING PSYCHOLOGICAL TRAUMA

279
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,040
"Female patient

280
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:41,960
suffering psychological trauma
caused by her half-brother's

281
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:48,120
inappropriate, incestuous behavior.

282
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,560
Attempted molestation.

283
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:58,920
Unlawful confinement.

284
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:02,080
Emotional coercion.

285
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:07,120
Possessive and controlling behavior."

286
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:18,480
This isn't real.

287
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,520
This isn't real.

288
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:25,760
This isn't real.

289
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:27,600
This isn't real.

290
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:30,440
No!

291
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:41,600
- This can't be true!
- Maysa.

292
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:42,640
What's going on?

293
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:44,520
This isn't real!

294
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,840
- Calm down.
- That bastard.

295
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,400
May.

296
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:51,280
- There are people around.
- This isn't real!

297
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:52,640
This isn't real!

298
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:53,960
May.

299
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,960
Calm down. Get a hold of yourself.

300
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:05,680
Calm down.

301
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:38,120
The poll says your approval rating
has dropped by over 30%.

302
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:42,080
The party's ratings are falling with you.

303
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:49,240
And Maysa is so stressed,
she had to call off filming.

304
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,440
Her fans won't be able
to help you anymore.

305
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:57,000
The only way out now is for you
to publicly apologize to Dharn.

306
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:02,840
Tomorrow I'll call the press.
Just stick to the script.

307
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:06,920
If you want to apologize to him so badly,

308
00:23:09,320 --> 00:23:11,360
then go do it yourself.

309
00:23:12,320 --> 00:23:15,440
If I could, I would have already.

310
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,720
I wouldn't let the votes drop like this.

311
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:22,200
Do you know how hard it is
to build a voter base?

312
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,800
Why? Do you want to lose
the next election?

313
00:23:25,880 --> 00:23:29,120
And how can you be so sure
that apologizing

314
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:31,000
will fix anything?

315
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:36,080
Someone like Dharn,
give him an inch, and he'll take a mile.

316
00:23:37,560 --> 00:23:38,600
Once we admit fault,

317
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:41,760
he'll just use it as an excuse
to get closer to Fahsai anyway.

318
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:44,280
I'd rather let him
get close to your sister

319
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:46,520
than let you lose the election.

320
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:51,480
But there are better ways out.

321
00:23:56,240 --> 00:24:00,680
But you need to bring Fahsai
to the party anniversary event.

322
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:07,440
Then people will stop talking
about family issues.

323
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:13,080
Just seeing Fahsai next to us

324
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:16,360
will make people start questioning

325
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,400
whether Dharn might be
the problematic one.

326
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,400
Don't you order me around.

327
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:24,920
Have you even seen
your sister's condition?

328
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:26,640
And you still want her to help the party?

329
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:28,120
Dad.

330
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:31,360
Fahsai cares about you so much.

331
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:35,720
If you just approach her gently,

332
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:37,760
she'll soften.

333
00:24:41,040 --> 00:24:44,360
And I'm sure deep down,

334
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:47,360
she's not heartless enough
to cut ties with me completely.

335
00:24:49,560 --> 00:24:50,920
You have to talk to her.

336
00:24:52,720 --> 00:24:54,920
It's the only way we'll survive.

337
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:03,600
Is there really no way, Doctor,
to get Fahsai to attend the party event?

338
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,680
As a psychiatrist,

339
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:09,080
I cannot suggest that
to the patient directly.

340
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:12,680
However, you can ask
for Ms. Fahsai's consent first.

341
00:25:13,760 --> 00:25:15,080
But I strongly recommend

342
00:25:15,160 --> 00:25:18,360
prioritizing the patient's willingness.

343
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:21,880
If she's not ready,
it won't benefit anyone.

344
00:25:23,160 --> 00:25:24,360
Thank you, Doctor.

345
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:34,800
This year's
Namchat Thai Party anniversary,

346
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:36,680
everyone will be watching

347
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:38,760
to see if Minister Rakchat's family

348
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:40,400
will show up together like always.

349
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:43,000
Even when she was studying in the US,

350
00:25:43,080 --> 00:25:45,200
Ms. Fahsai flew back for it.

351
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:49,240
Now that she's in Thailand,
if she doesn't show…

352
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:51,640
Mahasamut will be completely torn apart.

353
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,240
His only way out

354
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:55,920
is to publicly apologize to us.

355
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:58,800
But if he still refuses to admit fault,

356
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:01,480
he can prepare to lose his MP seat.

357
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:05,720
That works for me.

358
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,720
One less competitor
without having to do anything.

359
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:14,280
You want me to attend the party event

360
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:17,320
with Samut?

361
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:20,320
Fahsai,

362
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:24,880
everyone expects our family
to appear together.

363
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:29,320
Otherwise, the media will blow this up.

364
00:26:31,680 --> 00:26:33,520
It'll damage our family

365
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:36,160
and the party.

366
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:40,040
Of course.

367
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,720
You want everyone to believe

368
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:46,360
our family is normal.

369
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:49,200
You want me to help you deceive them.

370
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:50,800
Fahsai.

371
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:58,240
Even though you know
exactly what happened?

372
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:01,400
Don't mention attending
an event with him yet.

373
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:04,000
I can't even

374
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:06,440
look at his face.

375
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,520
Fahsai,

376
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:15,520
I promise there won't be any problems.

377
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:18,640
Samut won't cause trouble.

378
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,080
Fahsai,

379
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,280
can't you do this for me

380
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:26,400
and for the party one more time?

381
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:36,160
Then can you do something
for me just once?

382
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:40,960
I don't want to go.

383
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,240
I don't want to see him.

384
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:47,840
I won't go. And I will never go.

385
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:18,040
- Excuse me.
- Come in.

386
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:22,120
Are you visiting Fahsai?

387
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:26,040
I'd like that too…

388
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:28,320
if she'd agree.

389
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,560
I came to see you.

390
00:28:33,920 --> 00:28:35,680
I can help you with Ms. Fahsai.

391
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:39,680
How?

392
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:44,480
If Ms. Fahsai

393
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:46,960
doesn't attend the party anniversary,

394
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:51,360
the media will confirm the family conflict

395
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,560
is real.

396
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:00,400
And the one who suffers most

397
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:03,240
won't just be Mr. Samut…

398
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:07,000
but the entire Namchat Thai Party.

399
00:29:18,320 --> 00:29:19,520
What's your condition?

400
00:29:22,840 --> 00:29:26,480
If I can get Ms. Fahsai to attend,

401
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:32,640
you must keep your promise
about that piece of land we discussed.

402
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:39,480
I thought you wanted that father
and son to be destroyed.

403
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:41,200
Why help them now?

404
00:29:43,040 --> 00:29:46,320
You have to tighten the threads first.

405
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,360
Hey.

406
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:52,240
I'm talking to you.

407
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:55,440
He already answered you.

408
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:07,760
Oh. So you need to dig deeper

409
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:10,400
and make them trust you more?

410
00:30:14,040 --> 00:30:14,880
Exactly.

411
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:19,760
Your brother doesn't just want Mahasamut
to lose the election

412
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:22,320
or get dragged through the mud online.

413
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:26,920
But you said yourself
Fahsai won't even see anyone.

414
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:29,080
How are you going to get her to the event?

415
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:36,280
There's one key

416
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:41,280
that might unlock Fahsai.

417
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:45,520
We need to try.

418
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:54,640
How dare he?

419
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:57,080
Who does he think he is,
telling Fahsai what to do?

420
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:59,560
Isn't it a good thing

421
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:02,400
if he can bring Fahsai to the event?

422
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,240
And who is he, exactly?
Why should Fahsai listen to him?

423
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:09,840
Samut.

424
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:13,480
This whole mess happened because of you.

425
00:31:15,680 --> 00:31:17,280
You wanted her at the event.

426
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:20,320
Now that someone's willing to help,

427
00:31:21,320 --> 00:31:22,360
you're unhappy again?

428
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:24,800
And what if he can't bring her?

429
00:31:25,400 --> 00:31:27,200
Then you'll look even more ridiculous.

430
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:29,440
He already knows
about our family problems.

431
00:31:30,040 --> 00:31:33,000
The one who should be ashamed is you.

432
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:36,240
You're the one who caused all of this.

433
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:39,640
Try looking at yourself for once.

434
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:45,040
I don't know whether Wayu
can bring your sister to the event or not,

435
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:48,080
but he's the last card we have left.

436
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:51,320
Or do you think you can do it?

437
00:31:55,520 --> 00:32:00,000
I think you'd be better off spending time
writing a script for answering the press.

438
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:13,120
Today marks the 32nd anniversary
of the founding of the Namchat Thai Party.

439
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:16,000
Distinguished guests
are gradually arriving at the event.

440
00:32:16,080 --> 00:32:19,560
What's noticeable this time
is that Minister Rakchat

441
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:22,600
is not personally out here welcoming
the senior guests like he usually does.

442
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:26,360
Meanwhile, MP Mahasamut and Ms. Fahsai
are on their way to the event.

443
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,120
Sir,

444
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:34,520
the reporters are already talking about
the fact that Ms. Fahsai and Mr. Mahasamut

445
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,760
still haven't arrived.

446
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:39,360
And also,

447
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,400
that you aren't out there
receiving the senior guests.

448
00:32:45,040 --> 00:32:46,320
Have you been able to reach Wayu?

449
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,600
He's not answering, sir.

450
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,800
Then contact Mahasamut.

451
00:32:56,680 --> 00:33:00,160
Mr. Samut, may we have a quick interview?

452
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:03,280
Ms. Fahsai normally attends
the party anniversary every year.

453
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:05,520
Why isn't she here this year?

454
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:08,400
Or is it because
of your problem with Mr. Dharn?

455
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:11,000
Please answer the question.

456
00:33:11,080 --> 00:33:14,440
Is it true that there's conflict
between you and Ms. Fahsai?

457
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:15,760
Yeah.

458
00:33:15,840 --> 00:33:17,280
The reason Fahsai isn't here today

459
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:19,000
is simply because she's sick. That's all.

460
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:21,160
So there's no family problem, right,

461
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,400
Mr. Mahasamut?

462
00:33:23,320 --> 00:33:27,080
Do you want me to arrange a press visit
so you can go see Fahsai yourselves?

463
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:31,400
I already told you my sister is ill.

464
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:33,960
If she's that unwell,
how could anyone bring her here?

465
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:36,200
Oh.

466
00:33:47,120 --> 00:33:48,200
That's Ms. Fahsai.

467
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:49,280
Where?

468
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:51,640
- Oh?
- That's really her.

469
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,760
- She actually came.
- I thought she was sick.

470
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,200
- She's here.
- Ms. Fahsai.

471
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:57,480
May we have an interview?

472
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:03,280
I'm right here beside you.

473
00:34:09,239 --> 00:34:12,600
Ms. Fahsai, you haven't been out
helping with the campaign lately.

474
00:34:12,679 --> 00:34:15,120
Is it really because there's conflict?

475
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:18,880
I haven't been feeling well,
so I haven't been out campaigning.

476
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,679
Have you two already reconciled?

477
00:34:23,639 --> 00:34:25,920
Then why did Mr. Samut assault Mr. Dharn?

478
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:27,040
What was the reason?

479
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:28,480
Yeah.

480
00:34:35,159 --> 00:34:38,199
Please let Samut
be the one to clarify that.

481
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:40,639
Then after this,

482
00:34:40,719 --> 00:34:42,639
will you still be helping
with the campaign?

483
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:44,560
If there's really no family problem,

484
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:46,280
then you'll help your brother, right?

485
00:34:46,360 --> 00:34:48,199
- Right?
- Right?

486
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:50,320
- Could you answer the question?
- Please.

487
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:52,840
Even though I haven't been able
to go out campaigning

488
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:55,040
because of my health,

489
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:56,880
our family is still working for the party.

490
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,960
We're still working together
as a strong team.

491
00:35:02,160 --> 00:35:03,000
That's good.

492
00:35:03,080 --> 00:35:06,400
Then could we get a photo
of the siblings together,

493
00:35:06,480 --> 00:35:09,600
so the public can see that you've made up?

494
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,320
- Yes.
- Please.

495
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,120
Please let us take a photo
of you together.

496
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:15,240
- Please.
- Just one warm family shot, please.

497
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:17,320
- Please.
- Get the cameras ready.

498
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:19,960
Please let us take
a photo of you together.

499
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:57,880
This is our emergency signal.

500
00:36:00,480 --> 00:36:01,600
Just between you and me.

501
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:11,640
Your congratulations flowers.

502
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:13,320
Wow.

503
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,560
That bouquet is huge.

504
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:16,280
Let us get a shot of that.

505
00:36:16,360 --> 00:36:17,600
This camera, please.

506
00:36:17,680 --> 00:36:20,160
Please smile.

507
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:21,400
Please smile.

508
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:22,880
Please stay close to each other.

509
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:25,160
Please stand next to each other.

510
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:26,440
A little closer, please.

511
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:28,520
Beautiful. Very nice.

512
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:30,000
This camera, please.

513
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:31,120
This way, please.

514
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:33,320
This way too, please.

515
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:35,880
Ms. Fahsai needs to go rest now.

516
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:39,640
Alright.

517
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:41,480
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

518
00:36:41,560 --> 00:36:42,560
This way, please.

519
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:44,320
Wait.

520
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:49,400
Mr. Samut, you should stay
and speak with the reporters first.

521
00:36:53,040 --> 00:36:54,320
Please, go ahead.

522
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:09,240
Today's event was very well organized,

523
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:12,160
- Mr. Rakchat.
- Thank you very much.

524
00:37:12,760 --> 00:37:15,200
We should be heading back now.

525
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:17,600
- Alright. Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

526
00:37:17,680 --> 00:37:19,040
- Thank you so much.
- Of course.

527
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:19,960
Let's go.

528
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:22,200
That was good.

529
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:33,800
Where are you going?

530
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,080
Where's Fahsai?

531
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:57,520
I remembered your warning,

532
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,400
so I managed to get away in time.

533
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:02,400
Otherwise…

534
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:05,040
Ms. Fahsai,

535
00:38:05,680 --> 00:38:07,240
you made it out.

536
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:10,800
You were very brave.

537
00:38:13,160 --> 00:38:15,680
No, not at all.

538
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:20,240
Why didn't I realize it sooner?

539
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:21,520
Even if you had realized it,

540
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:25,240
that doesn't mean you could have
protected yourself every time.

541
00:38:28,200 --> 00:38:30,720
You were very lucky, Ms. Fahsai.

542
00:38:31,800 --> 00:38:34,680
Then how did you know about me?

543
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,400
You know about Ms. Fahsai

544
00:38:40,480 --> 00:38:42,440
and her brother, don't you?

545
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:45,280
Yes. I was the one who warned her.

546
00:38:47,720 --> 00:38:49,360
Because I didn't want her…

547
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:53,280
to end up like me.

548
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:56,080
Morn,

549
00:38:56,640 --> 00:38:58,720
I don't like this.
I'm not a little kid anymore.

550
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,480
I don't like you hanging around
with that guy either.

551
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:03,440
Morn, let go. I don't like this.

552
00:39:03,520 --> 00:39:06,240
- Stop!
- No one treats you better than I do.

553
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:07,800
- Mei.
- Let go!

554
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:09,120
Mei!

555
00:39:09,200 --> 00:39:11,880
Whose baby are you carrying?
Tell me right now.

556
00:39:11,960 --> 00:39:14,440
Mom, it's Morn.

557
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:16,120
Morn came onto me.

558
00:39:16,200 --> 00:39:17,160
You ungrateful child!

559
00:39:18,240 --> 00:39:19,880
And you still dare lie to me?

560
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:21,560
Morn already told me

561
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:24,480
you were fooling around
with a married man.

562
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:27,600
Why would you do this to me?
Why would you do this to me?

563
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:32,640
Mom, don't believe him.
Believe me. He's lying.

564
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:33,920
I don't believe you.

565
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,000
Your brother is a good man.

566
00:39:36,080 --> 00:39:38,760
He would never do
something so vile and disgusting.

567
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:42,920
So that's why you did what you did?

568
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,560
Yes.

569
00:39:45,720 --> 00:39:49,360
I admit it. I wanted to spite my mother
because she refused to believe me.

570
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:52,760
As for my brother,

571
00:39:52,840 --> 00:39:54,520
in front of Mom, he denied everything.

572
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:58,080
But behind her back, he kept trying

573
00:39:58,160 --> 00:39:59,480
to keep me close.

574
00:40:00,400 --> 00:40:01,920
He even lied to my mother,

575
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:04,120
saying my boyfriend
hadn't broken up with his wife yet,

576
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:06,000
just to keep me with him.

577
00:40:07,480 --> 00:40:08,720
I wanted to die.

578
00:40:13,960 --> 00:40:15,360
But after I met you,

579
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:20,400
you gave me hope again, Ms. Fahsai.

580
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,200
You gave me the strength

581
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:25,880
to want to start over.

582
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:40,400
But now I'm the one
who feels completely lost.

583
00:40:43,640 --> 00:40:45,200
I'm so confused.

584
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:49,240
My brother apologized to me.
He said he'd never do it again. But--

585
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:51,120
But you still don't trust him.

586
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:55,520
You don't trust him the way you used to.

587
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:00,160
My father says

588
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:03,120
my brother could
never think of me that way.

589
00:41:05,080 --> 00:41:07,840
And he made him move out.

590
00:41:07,920 --> 00:41:09,640
Ms. Fahsai,

591
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:11,640
at least

592
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:14,080
your father is still protecting you,

593
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:17,280
even if he still won't accept the truth.

594
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:31,800
But that only confuses me even more.

595
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:36,640
If we just cover up the truth that easily,
then what happens after this?

596
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:39,040
Will he really never do that again?

597
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:41,560
And what am I supposed to do?

598
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:44,520
Is there anyone who believes you
and listens to you?

599
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:47,280
Like how you listened to me
and helped me that day,

600
00:41:47,360 --> 00:41:50,080
without caring what my family said.

601
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:56,280
Ms. Fahsai.

602
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:05,120
Do you remember
why you were able to hold a gun?

603
00:42:07,120 --> 00:42:08,960
Why you weren't afraid of it?

604
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:12,000
Why you didn't collapse
the moment you saw it again?

605
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:16,680
What kept you in control?

606
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:22,080
If you don't want to spend
your whole life running from fear,

607
00:42:24,160 --> 00:42:27,360
then you have to turn around and face it.

608
00:42:28,800 --> 00:42:30,160
That's the only way

609
00:42:31,400 --> 00:42:33,200
to win back your own heart.

610
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:47,680
I still can't believe it

611
00:42:48,760 --> 00:42:50,520
that I actually dared to come today.

612
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,360
Dared to face Samut.

613
00:42:57,120 --> 00:43:00,000
I told you you could do it.

614
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:05,120
My father must be
very pleased with you after this.

615
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:11,000
I won't deny that.

616
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:14,120
But I should be thanking you

617
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:16,400
for agreeing to help.

618
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:22,480
You don't have to thank me.

619
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:25,480
I didn't want everyone else
to be caught up in trouble.

620
00:43:26,840 --> 00:43:28,440
I didn't want my father

621
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:31,920
or the people in the party
to be hurt because of me again.

622
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:48,240
It's not because of you.

623
00:43:51,560 --> 00:43:54,600
I'm thanking you
because you agreed to do it.

624
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:57,240
But even if you hadn't

625
00:43:58,080 --> 00:43:59,520
and they still suffered for it,

626
00:44:01,280 --> 00:44:02,240
you wouldn't be at fault.

627
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:07,800
Not even a little bit.

628
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:47,960
Thank you for believing me.

629
00:44:49,480 --> 00:44:51,040
Thank you for staying by my side.

630
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:34,680
Fahsai.

631
00:45:38,280 --> 00:45:39,320
Get inside and hide first.

632
00:45:46,880 --> 00:45:48,600
Ms. Fahsai isn't ready to see you yet.

633
00:45:49,200 --> 00:45:50,520
Move.

634
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:55,720
The more hot-headed you get,
the more you push her away.

635
00:45:55,800 --> 00:45:57,600
You should give her more time.

636
00:45:58,720 --> 00:46:00,200
Don't you dare lecture me.

637
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:01,960
Stop right now, Samut.

638
00:46:04,800 --> 00:46:08,200
If you're still this out of control,

639
00:46:08,280 --> 00:46:10,600
I won't let you see Fahsai again.

640
00:46:23,720 --> 00:46:25,400
I just want to talk to Fahsai.

641
00:46:25,480 --> 00:46:28,840
The fact that she agreed to attend
the event today was lucky enough already.

642
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:33,160
Learn to wait. Understand?

643
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:45,640
Why didn't you go to the event?

644
00:46:51,160 --> 00:46:53,440
You called me here just for that?

645
00:46:53,520 --> 00:46:56,040
Last time, you shut down production.

646
00:46:56,120 --> 00:46:57,840
Your fanbase took a hit.

647
00:46:58,960 --> 00:47:01,720
Instead of working harder
and polishing your image,

648
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:04,080
you keep ending up like this.

649
00:47:04,160 --> 00:47:06,560
No wonder he still won't marry you.

650
00:47:10,000 --> 00:47:11,920
The reason that man won't marry me

651
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:13,680
is not my fault.

652
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:17,600
It's because…

653
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:19,080
Because what?

654
00:47:24,600 --> 00:47:26,000
If it's just him being flirty,

655
00:47:27,400 --> 00:47:29,240
that's normal for men.

656
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:32,080
Especially men at his level.

657
00:47:33,320 --> 00:47:34,640
If it were only that,

658
00:47:35,320 --> 00:47:37,040
I could still endure it.

659
00:47:37,640 --> 00:47:38,880
No matter how painful.

660
00:47:39,560 --> 00:47:41,880
But this is twisted.

661
00:47:41,960 --> 00:47:43,480
He's beyond vile.

662
00:47:44,880 --> 00:47:45,920
What did he do to you?

663
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:49,360
He…

664
00:47:52,320 --> 00:47:53,800
He and Fahsai…

665
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:55,440
- He--
- You don't need to say it.

666
00:48:00,240 --> 00:48:01,640
Why not, Dad?

667
00:48:03,040 --> 00:48:04,040
I want to tell you.

668
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:06,160
Why won't you listen?

669
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:09,240
Are you going to tell me that no matter
how awful he is, I should ignore it?

670
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:11,600
And you're only realizing that now?

671
00:48:12,960 --> 00:48:15,560
Did you choose him
because he was a good man?

672
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:22,520
But this is about him trying
to rape his own sister, Dad.

673
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:27,680
If he hasn't beaten you,

674
00:48:29,360 --> 00:48:31,320
if he hasn't physically hurt you,

675
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:33,800
then I don't care what it is.

676
00:48:34,840 --> 00:48:37,400
The price we paid

677
00:48:37,480 --> 00:48:39,160
has to get us something in return.

678
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:42,200
So you can't afford to lose your position.

679
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:45,680
And what about you?

680
00:48:47,520 --> 00:48:49,720
Are you willing to lose
your lead actress spot?

681
00:48:52,440 --> 00:48:55,360
If it weren't for Mahasamut's connections,

682
00:48:55,440 --> 00:48:56,520
do you really think

683
00:48:57,480 --> 00:49:00,280
the people in this industry
would care about you?

684
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:14,720
The DNA results are out.

685
00:49:25,680 --> 00:49:28,120
That tooth from the corpse
doesn't belong to Peeraka.

686
00:49:28,200 --> 00:49:31,280
And the DNA doesn't match
his mom or Peekul either.

687
00:49:32,320 --> 00:49:33,640
So now everything's turned upside down.

688
00:49:34,360 --> 00:49:36,080
Whose corpse did they use
to fake the case?

689
00:49:39,080 --> 00:49:40,320
Captain,

690
00:49:40,400 --> 00:49:42,040
this case is no ordinary one.

691
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:46,240
Who the hell is behind this?

692
00:49:51,800 --> 00:49:53,400
We have to find out.

693
00:49:54,040 --> 00:49:57,840
Including whether Peeraka
may still be alive.

694
00:49:58,520 --> 00:49:59,440
I can't believe it.

695
00:49:59,520 --> 00:50:01,920
Minister Rakchat's daughter
really does have sharp instincts.

696
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:04,560
She knew this case
had something hidden in it.

697
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:10,560
Captain, have you called her

698
00:50:10,640 --> 00:50:12,080
about the DNA results yet?

699
00:50:26,960 --> 00:50:28,080
You.

700
00:50:30,600 --> 00:50:33,560
Do you think I should agree to see Samut?

701
00:50:35,520 --> 00:50:36,440
Why?

702
00:50:38,200 --> 00:50:41,400
Because you feel sorry for him?
Or because you feel sorry for me?

703
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:45,680
Or both?

704
00:50:48,840 --> 00:50:51,280
If I agree to see him, maybe he'll feel

705
00:50:51,360 --> 00:50:53,560
less stressed and stop
taking it out on you so much.

706
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:58,320
Or it might just make him think
you'll always forgive him quickly.

707
00:51:01,160 --> 00:51:02,440
Men are all conceited.

708
00:51:05,720 --> 00:51:06,840
I'm not stopping you

709
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:10,720
if you want to be kind to him
to make him feel better.

710
00:51:11,880 --> 00:51:12,880
But I'm worried

711
00:51:12,960 --> 00:51:14,600
that once he feels comfortable,

712
00:51:15,800 --> 00:51:17,760
he'll start acting on his impulses again.

713
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:40,360
Captain.

714
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:45,560
What good timing.

715
00:51:48,720 --> 00:51:50,160
You're off work already, aren't you?

716
00:51:50,920 --> 00:51:53,280
Not exactly. I was actually
about to go run an errand.

717
00:51:54,080 --> 00:51:56,200
Did you need something, Ms. Prapai?

718
00:52:02,480 --> 00:52:04,240
I've wanted to eat here for ages,

719
00:52:04,320 --> 00:52:05,840
but I didn't want to come alone,

720
00:52:05,920 --> 00:52:07,720
so I had to trouble you, Captain.

721
00:52:07,800 --> 00:52:09,560
No trouble at all.

722
00:52:09,640 --> 00:52:13,960
Consider it my treat in return
for helping me with the case last time.

723
00:52:16,920 --> 00:52:18,560
Oh, I think

724
00:52:18,640 --> 00:52:20,400
I should order some food
for my family too.

725
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:22,640
What should I order for them?

726
00:52:24,360 --> 00:52:25,400
My battery's dead.

727
00:52:45,200 --> 00:52:47,520
Go ahead.

728
00:52:57,520 --> 00:52:58,640
Call them.

729
00:53:01,160 --> 00:53:02,600
It's really noisy in here.

730
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:04,320
I'll just step away for a second.

731
00:53:04,400 --> 00:53:05,600
Wait.

732
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:08,200
I've got something that can help.

733
00:53:08,880 --> 00:53:10,520
Technology to the rescue.

734
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:16,000
This model blocks out outside noise.

735
00:53:23,920 --> 00:53:26,080
- How is it?
- It blocks really well.

736
00:53:27,280 --> 00:53:28,120
Go ahead and call.

737
00:53:31,800 --> 00:53:32,760
Hey, careful.

738
00:53:33,480 --> 00:53:34,800
I'm so sorry.

739
00:53:34,880 --> 00:53:37,120
My clothes are completely stained.

740
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:38,880
I need to go to the restroom.

741
00:53:38,960 --> 00:53:40,440
Sorry.

742
00:53:49,160 --> 00:53:51,160
Who did he send the DNA results to?

743
00:54:00,840 --> 00:54:02,040
Hey.

744
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:06,760
You need any help in there? Are you okay?

745
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:09,880
Just a second.

746
00:54:30,120 --> 00:54:32,480
Who is user Justice13?

747
00:54:32,560 --> 00:54:34,880
There's no profile picture,
no details, nothing.

748
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:39,800
But Captain Anawin set up a meeting
with them to hand over the DNA results.

749
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:43,560
He didn't mention the place,
didn't mention the time,

750
00:54:43,640 --> 00:54:45,760
and all the earlier chat history
was deleted too.

751
00:54:45,840 --> 00:54:48,480
That's why he let you
borrow his phone so easily.

752
00:54:49,200 --> 00:54:51,920
He'd already hidden everything
about the person he was talking to.

753
00:54:54,640 --> 00:54:57,040
Fahsai also secretly went
to meet Captain Anawin before.

754
00:54:59,160 --> 00:55:00,360
You mean to say

755
00:55:01,080 --> 00:55:04,000
Fahsai is the one who asked
Captain Anawin to investigate this case?

756
00:55:12,240 --> 00:55:13,600
That body wasn't Peeraka's.

757
00:55:15,040 --> 00:55:17,480
I still can't believe it.

758
00:55:18,680 --> 00:55:22,240
If it weren't for the DNA result
from the tooth, I wouldn't have believed

759
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:25,480
the case could've been closed
in a way that didn't match the facts.

760
00:55:26,600 --> 00:55:29,160
Someone must've wanted this whole thing
buried as fast as possible.

761
00:55:29,240 --> 00:55:31,280
That's why they faked evidence
that Peeraka was dead.

762
00:55:31,360 --> 00:55:33,360
There are still several possibilities.

763
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:35,440
But we can't conclude anything yet.

764
00:55:40,560 --> 00:55:43,440
Do you think it's possible

765
00:55:43,520 --> 00:55:45,360
that he might still be alive?

766
00:55:47,960 --> 00:55:49,400
As long as we haven't found the body,

767
00:55:51,240 --> 00:55:53,000
then I can say

768
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:54,880
it's possible.

769
00:55:57,880 --> 00:55:59,400
I want you to reopen this case.

770
00:55:59,480 --> 00:56:01,040
I definitely will,

771
00:56:01,880 --> 00:56:03,400
if I find that Peeraka wasn't guilty.

772
00:56:08,240 --> 00:56:11,600
But I'm pretty sure

773
00:56:13,800 --> 00:56:15,240
there's something behind all this.

774
00:56:17,480 --> 00:56:19,000
So for now,

775
00:56:19,080 --> 00:56:21,240
I want us to keep this between us.

776
00:56:22,840 --> 00:56:24,160
Okay.

777
00:56:34,680 --> 00:56:37,200
I will prove the truth of this matter.

778
00:56:54,560 --> 00:56:56,760
Why are you waking me up this early, Bua?

779
00:56:57,720 --> 00:56:59,720
It's me.

780
00:57:01,000 --> 00:57:03,280
- Well.
- Yong?

781
00:57:07,520 --> 00:57:08,360
You!

782
00:57:15,360 --> 00:57:17,560
Shouldn't you tell me first before coming?

783
00:57:17,640 --> 00:57:19,840
I was afraid that if I told you,
I wouldn't get to come.

784
00:57:21,680 --> 00:57:23,640
We have something important to discuss.

785
00:57:25,520 --> 00:57:27,440
I'm going back to sleep.

786
00:57:32,840 --> 00:57:34,960
The Minister has given you the green light

787
00:57:35,040 --> 00:57:36,320
to go back to work

788
00:57:36,400 --> 00:57:38,800
- at the foundation. Starting today.
- Really?

789
00:57:38,880 --> 00:57:40,120
- Yes.
- Yes.

790
00:57:44,560 --> 00:57:46,320
You think Fahsai should go back to work?

791
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:50,080
Right now, Ms. Fahsai is opening up
and can even attend public events.

792
00:57:50,960 --> 00:57:53,240
I'm worried that if we keep her
shut in that room,

793
00:57:53,320 --> 00:57:57,840
she may go back to how she was before.

794
00:57:57,920 --> 00:58:02,120
- I think we should push her a little more.
- Are you sure this won't make her worse?

795
00:58:02,200 --> 00:58:06,000
I'll take good care of her.
You have my word.

796
00:58:12,280 --> 00:58:15,480
But it was Dad who agreed, not me.

797
00:58:19,160 --> 00:58:20,640
But when you attended the party event,

798
00:58:21,240 --> 00:58:22,520
everyone assumed you were doing better.

799
00:58:22,600 --> 00:58:24,480
If you still don't go back to work,

800
00:58:26,160 --> 00:58:28,560
what are we supposed to tell
the foundation's partners?

801
00:58:29,640 --> 00:58:30,640
Exactly.

802
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:34,160
Ms. Fahsai.

803
00:58:35,680 --> 00:58:37,080
Please come back.

804
00:58:39,120 --> 00:58:40,800
I'm still not ready.

805
00:58:42,400 --> 00:58:44,760
I figured that would be your answer.

806
00:58:45,840 --> 00:58:47,960
So we're going to help
get you ready ourselves.

807
00:58:52,160 --> 00:58:53,560
If your body is strong,

808
00:58:53,640 --> 00:58:56,840
your mind will be more alert
and stronger too.

809
00:58:57,520 --> 00:58:58,880
I'll teach you

810
00:58:58,960 --> 00:59:02,480
how to defend yourselves
against someone physically stronger.

811
00:59:02,560 --> 00:59:04,880
Remember, everyone has weak points.

812
00:59:05,560 --> 00:59:07,760
- Ms. Yong, please help me demonstrate.
- Yes.

813
00:59:07,840 --> 00:59:09,360
Alright.

814
00:59:09,440 --> 00:59:11,360
- Turn around.
- Okay.

815
00:59:12,120 --> 00:59:15,960
Let's say this is a simulation where
the attacker has you locked from behind.

816
00:59:16,040 --> 00:59:18,280
Do you have a girlfriend?

817
00:59:18,360 --> 00:59:20,760
Do you have a girlfriend?

818
00:59:20,840 --> 00:59:22,160
Do you have a girlfriend?

819
00:59:22,240 --> 00:59:23,800
- Ms. Yong.
- Yes?

820
00:59:23,880 --> 00:59:25,320
This move simulates

821
00:59:25,400 --> 00:59:27,080
an attacker locking you from behind.

822
00:59:27,160 --> 00:59:29,120
Sorry. I'm focused. I'm alert.

823
00:59:29,200 --> 00:59:30,080
For this move,

824
00:59:30,160 --> 00:59:31,960
use both hands

825
00:59:32,040 --> 00:59:34,440
to slide along both
of the attacker's hands

826
00:59:34,960 --> 00:59:37,160
as if you're going along with it.

827
00:59:37,240 --> 00:59:38,440
The goal is

828
00:59:38,520 --> 00:59:41,560
to find the longest finger, which is?

829
00:59:42,120 --> 00:59:43,680
- The middle finger.
- Right.

830
00:59:43,760 --> 00:59:45,400
Once you grab them,
stretch them like this.

831
00:59:45,480 --> 00:59:46,400
- Yes.
- Stretch them.

832
00:59:46,480 --> 00:59:48,960
Then headbutt the attacker in the face.

833
00:59:49,040 --> 00:59:51,880
Good. Then stomp with your foot. Exactly.

834
00:59:51,960 --> 00:59:53,720
And then you can break free easily.

835
00:59:54,480 --> 00:59:55,840
Ms. Fahsai.

836
00:59:57,520 --> 00:59:59,720
Please go ahead, Ms. Fahsai. Oh, wait.

837
00:59:59,800 --> 01:00:00,920
Wait.

838
01:00:01,000 --> 01:00:02,800
Let me record a video too,

839
01:00:02,880 --> 01:00:04,440
in case I forget.

840
01:00:05,040 --> 01:00:06,600
- Alright.
- Okay.

841
01:00:08,320 --> 01:00:09,520
Turn around.

842
01:00:16,440 --> 01:00:17,840
This is a simulation.

843
01:00:20,480 --> 01:00:22,560
If an attacker grabs you from behind,

844
01:00:22,640 --> 01:00:23,720
what do you do?

845
01:00:28,560 --> 01:00:29,680
You like it when I hold you, don't you?

846
01:00:37,760 --> 01:00:38,640
Hey.

847
01:00:38,720 --> 01:00:43,080
Hey, I didn't mean to. Why did you
have to tease me like that first?

848
01:00:44,760 --> 01:00:46,440
Did it hurt a lot? I'm sorry.

849
01:00:54,400 --> 01:00:55,600
That was strong.

850
01:00:56,440 --> 01:00:58,240
Amazing.

851
01:00:59,560 --> 01:01:00,400
Were you messing with me?

852
01:01:01,480 --> 01:01:03,000
It really did hurt.

853
01:01:03,080 --> 01:01:04,200
That was hard.

854
01:01:04,280 --> 01:01:05,480
You want another one?

855
01:01:10,800 --> 01:01:11,920
What are you laughing at?

856
01:01:26,520 --> 01:01:27,800
If someone grabs you like this,
what do you do?

857
01:01:36,680 --> 01:01:38,280
Let go!

858
01:01:42,240 --> 01:01:43,160
Gosh.

859
01:01:44,920 --> 01:01:46,400
There's something else I want to know.

860
01:01:46,480 --> 01:01:48,160
What is it?

861
01:01:48,240 --> 01:01:51,000
It's about what you said,
that you love Wayu.

862
01:01:52,280 --> 01:01:53,320
Was that true?

863
01:01:54,760 --> 01:01:56,600
What I'm about to do is clarify the facts

864
01:01:57,440 --> 01:02:00,080
about what happened that day,
so everyone will know the truth.

865
01:02:04,840 --> 01:02:07,480
Mr. Dharn, is the man
in the clip really you?

866
01:02:07,560 --> 01:02:09,840
- Is that you?
- Mr. Dharn.

867
01:02:09,920 --> 01:02:11,600
- Come here.
- Hey!

868
01:02:11,680 --> 01:02:12,520
You've been putting ideas
in my sister's head, right?

869
01:02:12,600 --> 01:02:14,120
Samut!

870
01:02:14,920 --> 01:02:16,880
If you're going to shoot Wayu,
shoot me first.

871
01:02:17,560 --> 01:02:19,880
- Fahsai?
- I love him.

872
01:02:23,240 --> 01:02:26,360
SPECIAL THANKS

873
01:03:17,560 --> 01:03:20,560
